* https://biteeatrepeat.com/2022/05/28/ready-for-a-crab-santhemum-we-go-off-the-menu-and-dive-into-the-secret-swan-oyster-depot-menu-in-san-francisco-seafood-as-art/

## Notable "Secret" Dishes ~ not on the menu

* Sicilian sashimi: Thinly sliced raw salmon, tuna, yellowtail, and scallops drizzled with olive oil and topped with sea salt, pepper, shallots, and capers.
* The Maverick: a pound of crab, a filet of smoked trout and exactly 4 prawns
* A Dozen Eggs: A preparation of raw scallops served over ponzu sauce and topped with a dot of Sriracha.
* Crabsanthemum: Dungeness crab leg meat arranged to look like a flower.
* Smørrebrød, a.k.a. Open-faced Sandwich: Louie dressing on the bread so it soaks in, then top with lettuce and a mix of fresh seafood.
* Hot Lobster Salad: sweet lobster meat in a salad
* Combination Salad Sandwich
* Uni Sashimi: fresh sea urchin served raw
* Supreme Cocktail: Served in a large chowder bowl. 3.5 normal cocktails.
* Red Eye: A Saturday-morning-only cocktail with Bud Light, cocktail sauce, lemon juice, and other seasonings.
* Ask for the **olive oil and vinegar sauce**